Consol Glass says it's indefinitely suspended construction of a R1.5-billion manufacturing plant in Ekurhuleni. It says there’s been reduced demand for glass products due to the COVID-19 pandemic and lockdown. Consol Glass CEO Mike Arnold spoke to Devan Murugan. JOHANNESBURG - The alcohol ban and lockdown restrictions continue to take a toll on investment. Consol Glass says it's indefinitely suspended construction of a R1.5-billion manufacturing plant in Ekurhuleni. It says there’s been reduced demand for glass products due to the COVID-19 pandemic and the lockdown. READ: SAB cans investments worth billions On Monday, South Africa Breweries pulled the plug on investments worth R2.5-billion due to the impact of the alcohol ban. It’s reviewing equally valued investments for next year. Watch the video above for more details.